# Variables üì¶

Variables are containers for storing data.

## 3 Ways to Declare
1. `var` (Old, function-scoped)
2. `let` (Modern, block-scoped, mutable)
3. `const` (Modern, block-scoped, immutable)

```javascript
let name = "John";
const pi = 3.14;
var age = 25;

name = "Jane"; // Allowed
// pi = 3.15; // Error!
```

# String Operations üß∂

You can use `+` to join strings.

```javascript
let text1 = "Hello";
let text2 = "World";
let text3 = text1 + " " + text2;
```

## Template Literals (Modern)
Use backticks and `${}`.

```javascript
let text3 = `${text1} ${text2}!`;
```
